with tears in my eyes in the hospital,

766
00:42:28,921 --> 00:42:31,640
"My father is never going
to come near that child,

767
00:42:31,758 --> 00:42:34,602
because of the damage he did to me."

768
00:42:41,059 --> 00:42:44,063
INTERVIEWER:
Can I move on to your own acting career

769
00:42:44,187 --> 00:42:46,565
and how your moral beliefs
have affected it?

770
00:42:46,731 --> 00:42:50,577
<i>For example, we associate you
with roles like On the Waterfront,</i>

771
00:42:50,693 --> 00:42:54,072
where you are a man
who is fighting a righteous cause,

772
00:42:54,197 --> 00:42:55,289
a sort of underdog,

773
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:57,500
you've got the whole union machine
against you,

774
00:42:57,658 --> 00:43:00,411
<i>and then there's the roles
like the rebel leader in Viva Zapata!</i>

775
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:02,080
Where you are for the poor.

776
00:43:02,246 --> 00:43:03,964
Do you deliberately choose these roles?

777
00:43:04,082 --> 00:43:08,258
Over your career you've deliberately
chosen roles that have

778
00:43:08,377 --> 00:43:10,505
gone along with your political beliefs?

779
00:43:10,713 --> 00:43:12,260
Yes, I think so.

780
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:20,982
NARRATOR: On December 23rd, 1787,

781
00:43:21,099 --> 00:43:23,522
His Majesty's ship, Bounty,
sailed from England

782
00:43:23,643 --> 00:43:25,361
bound for the South Seas,

783
00:43:25,478 --> 00:43:27,901
culminating in the most famous mutiny
in history.

784
00:43:28,022 --> 00:43:29,990
CAPTAIN BLIGH:
You can put it in one word. Fear.

785
00:43:30,108 --> 00:43:31,985
Fear of punishment so vivid in his mind

786
00:43:32,110 --> 00:43:33,908
that he fears it even more
than certain death.

787
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:36,201
In my years of service,
I have never met an officer

788
00:43:36,322 --> 00:43:39,872
who inflicted punishment upon men
with such incredible relish.

789
00:43:41,369 --> 00:43:42,541
It's sickening.

790
00:43:43,538 --> 00:43:47,418
Then go and be sick in your cabin,
Mr Christian.

791
00:43:47,542 --> 00:43:48,964
BRANDO: Human hatred.

792
00:43:49,085 --> 00:43:50,337
What is the answer?

793
00:43:50,461 --> 00:43:53,055
Is there any answer to injustice?

794
00:43:53,172 --> 00:43:56,722
I wanted to make pictures
that are meaningful to me.

795
00:43:56,843 --> 00:43:59,062
CAPTAIN BLIGH:
You'd best join my war, Mr Christian,

796
00:43:59,178 --> 00:44:00,771
for if I don't start winning soon,

797
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:02,890
the casualty list will be real enough.

798
00:44:04,183 --> 00:44:07,562
BRANDO: You bring part of yourself
to every character,

799
00:44:07,728 --> 00:44:11,403
but some parts
are closer to us than others.

800
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:18,994
Is the story true about
you going to school in Minneapolis?

801
00:44:19,115 --> 00:44:22,335
I went to a military academy called...

802
00:44:24,036 --> 00:44:26,130
Well, I won't tell you the name.

803
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:27,499
I had a terrible time there.

804
00:44:29,792 --> 00:44:33,342
BRANDO: My father sent me
to military school, away from home,

805
00:44:33,462 --> 00:44:36,557
the one he had attended.

806
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:39,894
It was a cruel and unusual punishment.

807
00:44:42,138 --> 00:44:45,187
The mind of the military has one aim:

808
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:48,895
to be as mechanical as possible.

809
00:44:49,979 --> 00:44:52,732
To function like a human machine.

810
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:57,904
Individuality simply did not exist.

811
00:44:59,989 --> 00:45:02,208
I had a lot of loneliness.

812
00:45:04,035 --> 00:45:07,756
I spent most of the time
up in the library

813
00:45:07,872 --> 00:45:12,628
reading the National Geographic
magazine about Tahiti.

814
00:45:13,753 --> 00:45:17,599
I was entranced
by the expressions on their faces.

815
00:45:17,757 --> 00:45:20,180
They had unmanaged faces,

816
00:45:20,301 --> 00:45:22,554
no manicured expressions.

817
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:23,937
A kindness.

818
00:45:26,098 --> 00:45:27,520
That's where I want to go,

819
00:45:27,642 --> 00:45:29,235
that's where I want to be.

820
00:45:38,611 --> 00:45:41,455
<i>When I made Mutiny on the Bounty,</i>

821
00:45:41,572 --> 00:45:44,826
finally I got a chance to go to Tahiti.

822
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:58,093
I'd fallen in love with Tahiti.

823
00:45:58,214 --> 00:46:00,091
It was everything I longed for,

824
00:46:00,216 --> 00:46:02,344
everything I hoped it would be.

825
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:08,482
As soon as they'd say cut,

826
00:46:08,599 --> 00:46:11,148
I'd take off my jacket,
dive into the water

827
00:46:11,269 --> 00:46:14,899
and swim under the boats
and play on the beach.

828
00:46:17,483 --> 00:46:20,953
The sky... I've never see a sky like it.

829
00:46:21,070 --> 00:46:24,870
And the sunsets defy words.

830
00:46:24,991 --> 00:46:27,119
My God.

831
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:31,088
I've only been here a short time.

832
00:46:31,205 --> 00:46:33,583
I have been puzzled
every time I see Tahitians,

833
00:46:33,708 --> 00:46:36,632
because I can't figure out
what they're thinking.

834
00:46:36,794 --> 00:46:40,173
When you watch Tahitians,
it's like watching a wave,

835
00:46:40,298 --> 00:46:43,598
or the wind in the palm tree,
or the palm tree itself.

836
00:46:44,802 --> 00:46:47,146
They'll bring their drums
and their skirts,

837
00:46:47,263 --> 00:46:48,480
and they'll laugh and dance

838
00:46:48,639 --> 00:46:50,562
and drink and make love.

839
00:46:50,725 --> 00:46:52,443
Full of laughter.

840
00:46:56,063 --> 00:46:57,315
CAPTAIN BLIGH: Mr Christian.

841
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:01,744
Kindly satisfy your lust elsewhere.

842
00:47:03,070 --> 00:47:05,664
Quite actually, sir,
we were simply discussing...

843
00:47:05,823 --> 00:47:06,915
Acknowledge the order.

844
00:47:09,076 --> 00:47:11,704
Lust to be satisfied elsewhere, sir.

845
00:47:11,871 --> 00:47:13,418
Report on board immediately.

846
00:47:17,251 --> 00:47:19,504
You bloody fool.

847
00:47:21,881 --> 00:47:25,135
<i>BRANDO: Mutiny on the Bounty
was perhaps my very worst experience</i>

848
00:47:25,259 --> 00:47:27,227
in making a motion picture.

849
00:47:27,345 --> 00:47:31,191
I never want to do that kind of picture
again as long as I live.

850
00:47:32,975 --> 00:47:35,148
Nobody was agreed when we went in.

851
00:47:35,269 --> 00:47:38,614
We all knew that it was impossible
to shoot that story.

852
00:47:38,731 --> 00:47:41,530
It won't work. That will never work.

853
00:47:41,650 --> 00:47:45,621
You can't have Christian standing aside
not doing anything.

854
00:47:45,738 --> 00:47:48,457
Keep him alive in the story.

855
00:47:49,617 --> 00:47:55,044
<i>I was never consulted
before the writing was done.</i>

856
00:47:55,164 --> 00:47:58,043
And I cared a great deal
about this picture.

857
00:47:59,919 --> 00:48:02,593
You put your life in the hands
of the director,

858
00:48:02,713 --> 00:48:04,590
because the director can screw you up.

859
00:48:04,757 --> 00:48:07,226
You're going too lightly, Quintal.

860
00:48:07,343 --> 00:48:09,562
Lay on with a will
or you'll take his place.

861
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:12,598
BRANDO: They can't direct actors,

862
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:15,476
they don't know what the process is.

863
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:21,199
How delicate it is
to create an emotional impression.

864
00:48:21,315 --> 00:48:25,991
They cover up their sense of inadequacy
by being very authoritative,

865
00:48:26,112 --> 00:48:28,365
commanding things.

866
00:48:28,489 --> 00:48:31,959
INTERVIEWER: Didn't he say he wanted
to talk to you and explain it to you?

867
00:48:32,076 --> 00:48:36,172
BRANDO: He wanted to give me
a long "no", and I favor short "noes".

868
00:48:36,288 --> 00:48:37,335
INTERVIEWER: No, I did...

869
00:48:37,456 --> 00:48:40,960
BRANDO: You can't argue with somebody
who's made up their mind.

870
00:48:41,836 --> 00:48:44,555
Don't ever be intimidated by directors.

871
00:48:47,758 --> 00:48:50,682
You bloody bastard.

872
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:52,976
You'll not put your foot on me again.

873
00:48:53,097 --> 00:48:56,522
There was a great deal of friction,
confusion and desperation,

874
00:48:56,642 --> 00:48:58,440
disappointment and disgust,

875
00:48:58,561 --> 00:48:59,858
there were fist fights.

876
00:49:00,062 --> 00:49:02,235
Ship's company!

877
00:49:02,356 --> 00:49:04,279
I'm taking command of this ship.

878
00:49:04,400 --> 00:49:06,528
Mr Friar, I'll have the keys
to the arms chest.

879
00:49:06,652 --> 00:49:08,495
You'll give him nothing!

880
00:49:08,612 --> 00:49:12,742
BRANDO:
Hey! I'm not your fucking stamp licker.

881
00:49:12,867 --> 00:49:14,665
You're making a huge error.

882
00:49:14,785 --> 00:49:16,002
Don't make it again.

883
00:49:16,120 --> 00:49:18,964
I don't care if it costs me my job.

884
00:49:19,206 --> 00:49:22,335
Marlon, talk about rage.

885
00:49:22,460 --> 00:49:25,054
Talk about your own rage.

886
00:49:25,171 --> 00:49:29,472
All my life I've questioned
why I should do something.

887
00:49:29,592 --> 00:49:31,344
I had contempt for authority.

888
00:49:31,469 --> 00:49:33,096
I would resist it, I would trick it,

889
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:35,723
I would outmaneuver it, I would do anything

890
00:49:35,848 --> 00:49:38,772
rather than be treated like a cipher.

891
00:49:39,477 --> 00:49:41,354
REPORTER:
Marlon Brando has been the subject

892
00:49:41,479 --> 00:49:43,982
of a good deal
of controversial publicity.

893
00:49:44,106 --> 00:49:45,824
He's been called a supreme egotist,

894
00:49:45,983 --> 00:49:47,610
uncooperative, temperamental.

895
00:49:47,735 --> 00:49:50,784
I've rarely seen
such a range of vicious critiques.

896
00:49:51,572 --> 00:49:55,622
BRANDO: They were blaming me
for all the delays and everything.

897
00:49:55,743 --> 00:49:57,461
They had to blame it on somebody,

898
00:49:57,578 --> 00:49:59,205
so they blamed it on me.

899
00:49:59,330 --> 00:50:02,504
Well, everybody has to have
a whipping boy and certainly the studio.

900
00:50:02,625 --> 00:50:04,798
They have to find a scapegoat,

901
00:50:04,919 --> 00:50:06,466
they have to find somebody.

902
00:50:06,587 --> 00:50:09,010
I was the most logical person.

903
00:50:09,798 --> 00:50:13,644
The sickening and endless variety
of lies.

904
00:50:13,761 --> 00:50:15,855
They can hit you every day

905
00:50:16,013 --> 00:50:18,641
and you have no way of fighting back.

906
00:50:19,934 --> 00:50:23,689
I was very convincing
in my pose of indifference.

907
00:50:25,105 --> 00:50:27,073
But I was very sensitive

908
00:50:27,191 --> 00:50:29,193
and it hurt a lot.

909
00:50:49,171 --> 00:50:50,514
There are times when you think,

910
00:50:50,631 --> 00:50:53,134
"What the fuck is all this for?"

911
00:50:53,259 --> 00:50:55,432
"Christ, nobody's listening."

912
00:50:56,804 --> 00:50:58,477
There's an old adage in Hollywood,

913
00:50:58,597 --> 00:51:01,271
they say "if you have a message,
go to Western Union."

914
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,358
I didn't make any great movies.

915
00:51:04,478 --> 00:51:06,401
There's no such thing as a great movie.

916
00:51:06,522 --> 00:51:08,445
In the kingdom of the blind,

917
00:51:08,566 --> 00:51:10,534
the man with one eye is the king.

918
00:51:11,944 --> 00:51:13,287
There are no artists.

919
00:51:13,445 --> 00:51:15,413
We are businessmen, we're merchants.

920
00:51:15,573 --> 00:51:17,667
And there is no art.

921
00:51:19,952 --> 00:51:22,671
Agents, lawyers, publicity people...

922
00:51:23,205 --> 00:51:25,424
It's all bullshit.

923
00:51:25,749 --> 00:51:27,501
Money, money, money.

924
00:51:27,626 --> 00:51:29,845
If you think it's about something else,

925
00:51:29,962 --> 00:51:32,511
you're going to be bruised.

926
00:51:33,882 --> 00:51:36,431
I do want to ask you one thing
before we run out of time, Marlon.

927
00:51:36,552 --> 00:51:37,974
You've been quoted
in the papers as saying

928
00:51:38,137 --> 00:51:39,559
that you are going to abandon acting.

929
00:51:39,680 --> 00:51:41,182
Are you really going to do that?

930
00:51:41,307 --> 00:51:45,813
I feel that I'd like to pursue some
other interests that I have long had.

931
00:51:45,936 --> 00:51:47,529
And within two or three years,

932
00:51:47,646 --> 00:51:49,899
I will have come to the end
of my career.

933
00:51:51,358 --> 00:51:53,986
We're all gonna talk about civil rights,

934
00:51:54,194 --> 00:51:55,912
we're all gonna go on the television

935
00:51:56,030 --> 00:51:57,657
and say what we know,

936
00:51:57,781 --> 00:51:59,499
because the country is ignorant.

937
00:52:00,576 --> 00:52:02,624
(APPLAUSE)

938
00:52:04,622 --> 00:52:07,296
lam really moved and motivated

939
00:52:07,416 --> 00:52:10,966
by things that occur that are unjust.

940
00:52:12,630 --> 00:52:16,601
I've always hated
people trampling on other people.

941
00:52:19,762 --> 00:52:21,059
I was in a quandary,

942
00:52:21,263 --> 00:52:23,686
a philosophical quandary,
because I thought

943
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:27,528
if I am not my brother's keeper,
who am I?

944
00:52:27,645 --> 00:52:32,867
Where does my life end and my sense
of responsibility for other lives begin?

945
00:52:34,443 --> 00:52:39,290
Black bodies swinging
in the summer breeze,

946
00:52:39,406 --> 00:52:42,535
and the smell of burning death.

947
00:52:42,660 --> 00:52:44,287
You could stand so much of it

948
00:52:44,411 --> 00:52:45,503
and to see these people

949
00:52:45,621 --> 00:52:48,545
being beaten and kicked and spit on.

950
00:52:49,625 --> 00:52:51,627
That could've been my son lying there.

951
00:52:51,752 --> 00:52:55,006
And I'm going to do as much as I can.

952
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:58,096
I'm going to start right now

953
00:52:58,258 --> 00:53:02,308
to inform white people
of what they don't know.

954
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:04,557
The white man can't cool it

955
00:53:04,682 --> 00:53:06,810
because he's never dug it.

956
00:53:06,934 --> 00:53:08,982
And I am here to try to dig it.

957
00:53:10,396 --> 00:53:12,615
King was in Memphis at the time.

958
00:53:12,731 --> 00:53:18,454
He was striking for a small wage
increase for garbage collectors,

959
00:53:18,612 --> 00:53:21,912
which was one of the best jobs
a black man could get.

960
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:25,707
But I want you to know tonight

961
00:53:25,869 --> 00:53:30,090
that we as a people
will get to the Promised Land.

962
00:53:30,249 --> 00:53:31,751
BRANDO: That speech where he says,

963
00:53:31,875 --> 00:53:33,593
"I've been up to the mountain

964
00:53:33,711 --> 00:53:35,634
and I've seen the Promised Land."

965
00:53:35,754 --> 00:53:39,679
So I'm happy tonight,
I'm not worried about anything.

966
00:53:39,800 --> 00:53:41,894
I'm not fearing any man.

967
00:53:42,010 --> 00:53:45,310
BRANDO: "I don't know
if I'm gonna get there with you,

968
00:53:45,431 --> 00:53:47,433
but I am not afraid tonight."

969
00:53:49,810 --> 00:53:52,063
God, I still remember that.

970
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:54,357
Ah, Jesus. That's terrible.

971
00:53:54,481 --> 00:53:56,575
He knew he was going to get killed.

972
00:54:01,905 --> 00:54:05,580
REPORTER: Have you considered that
you may suffer bodily harm yourself?

973
00:54:11,457 --> 00:54:12,925
Yes.

974
00:54:13,876 --> 00:54:16,129
BRANDO: I'm standing up,
not for the black race,

975
00:54:16,295 --> 00:54:18,297
I'm standing up for the human race.

976
00:54:18,422 --> 00:54:21,471
All men are created equal.

977
00:54:21,592 --> 00:54:22,718
This is life and death,

978
00:54:22,843 --> 00:54:24,015
this is real life.

979
00:54:24,136 --> 00:54:26,855
We're talking about human relations,

980
00:54:26,972 --> 00:54:28,690
we're talking about human rights,

981
00:54:28,807 --> 00:54:31,777
racial issues and that's why I care.

982
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:49,829
Get any and all reports from the
South Pacific Commission in respect to

983
00:54:49,953 --> 00:54:53,833
discovering what plants grow well
on atolls.

984
00:54:53,957 --> 00:54:56,836
How to grow more vegetables
than you can imagine.

985
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:59,338
And whatever there is on wind power.

986
00:54:59,463 --> 00:55:02,637
We'll get the full library
of information

987
00:55:02,758 --> 00:55:04,305
from the South Pacific Commission.

988
00:55:11,225 --> 00:55:13,319
<i>It was after Mutiny on the Bounty.</i>

989
00:55:13,435 --> 00:55:16,439
I was up in the mountains on Tahiti.

990
00:55:16,563 --> 00:55:19,316
And this guy said, "Do you see
that little island out there?"

991
00:55:19,441 --> 00:55:21,193
And I said, "No, I can't see it."

992
00:55:22,110 --> 00:55:23,453
He says, "Can't you see it?"

993
00:55:23,570 --> 00:55:25,698
"it's called Tetiaroa."

994
00:55:29,910 --> 00:55:31,662
I never was in a place that told me

995
00:55:31,787 --> 00:55:34,336
to quit running the way this place does,

996
00:55:34,456 --> 00:55:36,458
the way these people do.

997
00:55:43,382 --> 00:55:48,183
If I've come closer to a sense
of peace, it would be there.

998
00:55:54,852 --> 00:55:57,401
I didn't think of myself
as an owner of the island,

999
00:55:57,521 --> 00:56:01,025
I just thought that I'd paid
for the privilege of visiting there.

1000
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:04,153
I had nothing to give to them.

1001
00:56:04,361 --> 00:56:06,580
They had everything to give to me.

1002
00:56:09,908 --> 00:56:11,376
They don't care who you are,

1003
00:56:11,493 --> 00:56:13,086
they don't care what you do.

1004
00:56:13,203 --> 00:56:15,422
They don't know
that you're a movie star.

1005
00:56:15,539 --> 00:56:16,882
They couldn't care less.

1006
00:56:16,999 --> 00:56:22,221
You cannot lay dollars down
on the table and buy their soul.

1007
00:56:22,921 --> 00:56:25,970
Very warm, loving people.

1008
00:56:26,091 --> 00:56:28,093
They come up and put their arm
around you,

1009
00:56:28,218 --> 00:56:30,437
come and kiss you for no reason at all.

1010
00:56:30,554 --> 00:56:32,397
They just take love for granted.

1011
00:56:33,015 --> 00:56:34,483
INTERVIEWER: ls there any actress

1012
00:56:34,641 --> 00:56:37,770
that you've especially enjoyed
working with, and why?

1013
00:56:37,895 --> 00:56:39,863
(BRANDO LAUGHS)

